title: [Blighted Forest, Treetop]
description: A natural stair is formed by overlapping branches, offering passage from the branches of one oak to its neighboring trees.  Leaves sway gently at the touch of a light breeze and birds flitter from limb to limb.  Below, a dense patch of nettle bushes entirely covers the forest floor.

A natural stair is formed by overlapping branches, offering passage from the branches of one oak to its neighboring trees.  Black leaves sway gently at the touch of a light breeze and tree frogs sing to the moon.  Below, a dense patch of nettle bushes entirely covers the forest floor.
paths: Obvious paths: northeast, east, southwest, west, northwest
